All Classes

  • All Classes Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    AuberGame  
    Button
    Render a button and also handle the pressing of said button.
    Civilian
    The Civilian is the passive entity in auber that allows for Infiltrators to blend in.
    GameEntity
    The GameEntity class is the abstract class from which all entities, including the player must inherit from.
    GameOverScreen
    The game over screen is the screen that the game is set to when a win/lose condition has been reached.
    GameScreen
    The main screen of the game, responsible for rendering entities and executing their functions.
    GameUi  
    Infiltrator
    The infiltrator is the enemy of the game, it will navigate from system to system and sabotage them until caught by the Player.
    LoadScreen
    the screen that saves can be loaded from
    MenuScreen
    The menu screen is the first screen that shows in the game and is responsible for controlling when the game begins.
    NavigationMesh
    The NavigationMesh class is a wrapper around a 2d array of Booleans representing which tiles within the game world are accessible.
    Npc
    Npc is the class from which all AI controlled GameEntitys must extend.
    Npc.States  
    PathNode
    A class that represents a node in a given pathfinding attempt.
    Player
    The player entity that the user controls.
    PowerUp
    The Power up which can be picked up by the player.
    PowerUp.PowerUpEffect  
    Projectile  
    Projectile.CollisionActions  
    Utils
    A collection of utility functions that don't belong within a specific class.
    World
    The world class stores information related to what is happening within the game world.
    World.SystemStates  
    World.Tiles
    An enum containing information about all dynamic/frequently accessed tiles.
